-- Yankees Acquire Outfielder Ichiro Suzuki From Seattle Mariners
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-07-23T22:34:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-23/yankees-acquire-outfielder-ichiro-suzuki-from-seattle-mariners.html
The New York Yankees acquired
outfielder  Ichiro Suzuki  in a trade with the Seattle Mariners.  Suzuki, 38, has played his entire 12-year Major League
Baseball career with the Mariners. The first Japan-born player
in MLB is a 10-time All Star with a .322 career batting average,
1,176 runs and 99 home runs, the Yankees said in an e-mailed
statement today.  The Yankees got Suzuki and cash for right-handed pitchers
D.J. Mitchell and Danny Farquhar, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  